HEADWORD: Cathay
<hw>Ca*thay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>China; -- an old name
for the Celestial Empire, said have been introduced by Marco Polo and to
be a corruption of the Tartar name for North China (<xex>Khitai</xex>,
the country of the Khitans.)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Better fifty years of Europe than a cycle of
<qex>Cathay</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cathead</ent>⟦br⟧
